                  </bibl>
                  <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa">вАПвАПвАПвАП„Ц„Щ„Ш„Р</ref>
                  <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa">„Р„Щ„§„Ш„Р</ref>
                  <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa">„Р„Х„І„Ш„Х</ref>
                  <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                     <quote>He replied to them: From your own [language] I will prove it to you: вАЬZeбє≠a Њ (live) epбє≠ah (seven), eбє≠ah (go) akбє≠o (eight)вАЭ (cf. Freedman / Simon I: 112)</quote>
                  </cit>
                  <note>= <bibl type="ancient">GenR 14,2 [I 127: 3]</bibl>; <bibl type="ancient">GenR 20,6 [I 189: 3]</bibl>; <bibl type="ancient">NumR 4,3</bibl>: <term xml:lang="jpa">„Р„Щ„§„Ш„Р</term> <term xml:lang="fjb"> Њypбє≠ Њ</term> <term xml:lang="rabbinic">epбє≠a Њ</term>; <bibl type="ancient">Tanh  Bemidbar 18</bibl>; <bibl type="ancient">TanhB Bemidbar 21</bibl></note>
               </cit>
               <cit type="example" xml:lang="jpa">
                  <quote>„Р„Ю' „Ь„Ф„Я „С„Ь„©„Х„Я „Щ„Х„Х„†„Щ„™ „Ц„Щ„Ш„Р „Р„Щ„§„Ш„Р, „Р„Щ„Ш„Р „Р„Х„І„Ш„Х</quote>
                  <bibl>
